"title": "2565: Jesus Christ, second coming of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2565",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ will return visibly and in glory at the end of history to raise the dead, judge the world, destroy all evil and opposition to God and consummate his kingdom. Believers are encouraged to be prepared for his return, waiting with eagerness and joy.</p>\n<h2>The second coming is foretold</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:13-Dan7:14\">DAN 7:13–7:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:2-Ps72:4\">PSA 72:2–72:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:4\">ISA 2:2–2:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:3\">MIC 4:1–4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:4-Isa11:9\">ISA 11:4–11:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:5\">ISA 40:5</a></p>\n<h3>By Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30\">MAT 24:30</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26\">MRK 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:27\">LUK 21:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27\">MAT 16:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31\">MAT 25:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:62\">MRK 14:62</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:40\">LUK 12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:3\">JHN 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:28\">JHN 14:28</a></p>\n<h3>By the angels at Jesus Christ's ascension</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:11\">ACT 1:11</a></strong></p>\n<h3>By the apostles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20\">PHP 3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:20-Acts3:21\">ACT 3:20–3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:7\">1CO 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:26\">1CO 11:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:10\">1TH 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:13\">1TH 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7-2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:7–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a></p>\n<h2>NT terms for the second coming</h2>\n<h3>``Parousia''</h3>\n<p>Meaning literally <code>presence'' or</code>coming'', the term was used in the NT world of a royal visit:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:3\">MAT 24:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:7-Jas5:8\">JAS 5:7–5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:4\">2PE 3:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:28\">1JN 2:28</a></p>\n<h3>``Apocalypsis''</h3>\n<p>Meaning literally <code>unveiling'',</code>apocalypsis'' suggests that the second coming will make visible that which is already true of Jesus Christ but presently hidden from human sight:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:30\">LUK 17:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:7\">1CO 1:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7\">2TH 1:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:7\">1PE 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:13\">1PE 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>``Epiphaneia''</h3>\n<p>Meaning literally <code>appearing'' or</code>manifestation'', the term suggests coming out into view from a hidden background:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:8\">2TH 2:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:14\">1TI 6:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:1\">2TI 4:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:13\">TIT 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>Events that will precede the second coming</h2>\n<h3>The universal preaching of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:14\">MAT 24:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:10\">MRK 13:10</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:7-Acts1:8\">ACT 1:7–1:8</a></p>\n<h3>The persecution of believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:9\">MAT 24:9</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:9\">MRK 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:12\">LUK 21:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:21\">MAT 24:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:19\">MRK 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:22\">MAT 24:22</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:20\">MRK 13:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:12-Mark13:13\">MRK 13:12–13:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:12-Matt24:13\">MAT 24:12–24:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:16-Luke21:17\">LUK 21:16–21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1\">2TI 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:14\">REV 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>Apostasy, nominal religion and godlessness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1\">1TI 4:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:10\">MAT 24:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:5\">2TI 3:1–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:3-2Pet3:4\">2PE 3:3–3:4</a></p>\n<h3>The revelation of the antichrist</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:18\">1JN 2:18</a></strong> <em>The antichrist is a name given to the one who will lead opposition to God's kingdom.  It appears to refer to an individual but may denote a corporate movement.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:20-Dan7:22\">DAN 7:20–7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:3-2Thess2:4\">2TH 2:3–2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:3\">1JN 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:1-Rev13:10\">REV 13:1–13:10</a></p>\n<h3>The appearance of false Christs and false prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:24\">MAT 24:24</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:22\">MRK 13:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:15\">MAT 7:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:5\">MAT 24:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:6\">MRK 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:8\">LUK 21:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:11\">MAT 24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:23\">LUK 17:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:7\">2JN 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Wars and rumours of wars</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:6-Matt24:7\">MAT 24:6–24:7</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:7-Mark13:8\">MRK 13:7–13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:9-Luke21:10\">LUK 21:9–21:10</a></p>\n<h3>Famines and earthquakes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:7-Matt24:8\">MAT 24:7–24:8</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:8\">MRK 13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:11\">LUK 21:11</a></p>\n<h3>Cosmic changes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:29\">MAT 24:29</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:24\">MRK 13:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:25-Luke21:26\">LUK 21:25–21:26</a></p>\n<h2>The timing of the second coming</h2>\n<h3>At God's appointed time</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:20-Acts3:21\">ACT 3:20–3:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36\">MAT 24:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:32\">MRK 13:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:20-Luke17:30\">LUK 17:20–17:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:7\">ACT 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Unexpectedly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:1-1Thess5:2\">1TH 5:1–5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:27\">MAT 24:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:24\">LUK 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:43-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:43–24:44</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:39-Luke12:40\">LUK 12:39–12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10\">2PE 3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:3\">REV 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:15\">REV 16:15</a></p>\n<h3>After a delay</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:5\">MAT 25:5</a></strong> <em>Part of a parable concerning the coming of Jesus Christ who is represented by the bridegroom.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:19\">MAT 25:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:3-2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:3–3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Imminently</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30-Matt24:34\">MAT 24:30–24:34</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26-Mark13:30\">MRK 13:26–13:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:27-Luke21:32\">LUK 21:27–21:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:22\">JHN 21:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:11-Rom13:12\">ROM 13:11–13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:8-Jas5:9\">JAS 5:8–5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:11\">REV 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:7\">REV 22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:20\">REV 22:20</a></p>\n<h2>The manner of the second coming</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's personal return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:11\">ACT 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:20\">ACT 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a></p>\n<h3>A visible and glorious return</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30\">MAT 24:30</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26\">MRK 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:27\">LUK 21:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:64\">MAT 26:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:9\">ACT 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>With the sound of a trumpet</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:31\">MAT 24:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:52\">1CO 15:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>With angels</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27\">MAT 16:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:31\">MAT 24:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7\">2TH 1:7</a></p>\n<h2>The purpose of the second coming</h2>\n<h3>To raise the dead</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:22-1Cor15:23\">1CO 15:22–15:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:28-John5:29\">JHN 5:28–5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:52\">1CO 15:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>To judge all people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:13\">PSA 96:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:9\">PSA 98:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:27\">MAT 16:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:1\">2TI 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:11-Rev20:15\">REV 20:11–20:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:12\">REV 22:12</a></p>\n<h3>To judge the wicked</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7-2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:7–1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:51\">MAT 24:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5\">ROM 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:15\">JUD 1:15</a></p>\n<h3>To separate the wicked from the righteous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31-Matt25:32\">MAT 25:31–25:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:40-Matt24:41\">MAT 24:40–24:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:34-Luke17:35\">LUK 17:34–17:35</a></p>\n<h3>To destroy all evil and opposition to God's kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:8\">2TH 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24-1Cor15:26\">1CO 15:24–15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">REV 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:14\">REV 20:14</a></p>\n<h3>To reward believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:46-Matt24:47\">MAT 24:46–24:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:37\">LUK 12:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:8\">2TI 4:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:1\">1JN 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>To gather the church together</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:3\">JHN 14:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:1\">2TH 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>To bring final salvation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:28\">LUK 21:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:28\">HEB 9:28</a></p>\n<h3>To transform the saints into his likeness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:51-1Cor15:52\">1CO 15:51–15:52</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20-Phil3:21\">PHP 3:20–3:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:4\">COL 3:4</a></p>\n<h3>To end the present age</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:3\">MAT 24:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24\">1CO 15:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:10\">2PE 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:12\">2PE 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>To restore and renew all things</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:21\">ACT 3:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:13\">2PE 3:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:1-Rev21:5\">REV 21:1–21:5</a></p>\n<h2>Reactions at Jesus Christ's second coming</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30\">MAT 24:30</a> <em>all peoples will mourn</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:10\">2TH 1:10</a> <em>His people will marvel.</em></p>\n<h2>Present implications of the second coming for believers</h2>\n<h3>They must always be watchful and ready</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:42-Matt24:44\">MAT 24:42–24:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:10\">MAT 25:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:35\">MRK 13:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:35-Luke12:36\">LUK 12:35–12:36</a></p>\n<h3>They must be faithful stewards</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:30\">MAT 25:14–25:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:12-Luke19:27\">LUK 19:12–19:27</a></p>\n<h3>They must eagerly expect his coming</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:7\">1CO 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:28\">LUK 21:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20\">PHP 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:13\">TIT 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>They must endure suffering with patient endurance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:13\">MAT 24:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:6-1Pet1:7\">1PE 1:6–1:7</a></p>\n<h3>They must wait patiently</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:10\">1TH 1:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:7-Jas5:8\">JAS 5:7–5:8</a></p>\n<h3>It is an incentive to holiness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2-1John3:3\">1JN 3:2–3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:4-Col3:5\">COL 3:4–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:14\">1TI 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:11\">2PE 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:23\">1JN 2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:28\">1JN 2:28</a></p>\n<h3>It is an incentive to mission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:1-2Tim4:2\">2TI 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:12\">2PE 3:12</a></p>",
